{"add":{"doc":{"id":"ede10d7ed7ff32b25eae77063a88b004d0f807b07aa26dbd557735cac4e86d9c","url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/37/Tram_interior_edit1.jpg/120px-Tram_interior_edit1.jpg","previous":[],"after":["A tram (also known as a tramcar, streetcar, trolley, or trolley car) is a rail vehicle that runs on tracks, commonly along public urban streets (called street running), and sometimes on separate rights of way. Since about the turn of the twentieth century, the most common type of tram has been the electric tram, running on what were once called electric street railways. Previously, horse-drawn trams (horsecars), and, to a lesser extent, steam-powered trams, were widely used in urban areas."]}}}